{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T17:45:28.810Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hypothesis testing"},{"type":"text","text":" is the cornerstone of statistical inference—a formal framework for evaluating claims or assumptions about a population by analyzing sample data. It involves making a decision between two competing hypotheses (null vs. alternative) using statistical evidence, allowing data scientists to determine whether observed effects are real or just due to random chance./09:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Hypothesis_Testing/9.01:"},{"type":"text","text":"Introduction_to_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core concept:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hypothesis testing"},{"type":"text","text":" involves making a decision about two competing hypotheses about a population parameter. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.jmp.com/en/statistics-knowledge-portal/inferential-statistics/hypothesis-testing","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"jmp"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Goal"},{"type":"text","text":": See if there is sufficient statistical evidence to reject a presumed "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"null hypothesis"},{"type":"text","text":" in favor of a conjectured "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"alternative hypothesis"},{"type":"text","text":"./09:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Hypothesis_Testing/9.01:"},{"type":"text","text":"Introduction_to_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The two hypotheses:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hypothesis"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Symbol"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it means"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Null hypothesis"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"H₀"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Assumed true initially; states \"no effect\" or \"no difference\" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.jmp.com/en/statistics-knowledge-portal/inferential-statistics/hypothesis-testing","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"jmp"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Alternative hypothesis"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"H₁ (or Hₐ)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What you want to prove; states \"there is an effect\" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.jmp.com/en/statistics-knowledge-portal/inferential-statistics/hypothesis-testing","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"jmp"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Comparing two ML models:\n  H₀: Model A accuracy = Model B accuracy (no difference)\n  H₁: Model A accuracy > Model B accuracy (Model A is better)\n\nTesting if a drug works:\n  H₀: Drug has no effect (mean recovery = baseline)\n  H₁: Drug has effect (mean recovery ≠ baseline) [web:241]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key terminology:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Term"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Definition"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test statistic"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Value computed from sample data used to make decision (e.g., t-statistic, z-score)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"p-value"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Probability of observing data as extreme as yours, assuming H₀ is true "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.jmp.com/en/statistics-knowledge-portal/inferential-statistics/hypothesis-testing","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"jmp"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Significance level (α)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Threshold for deciding if evidence is strong enough (commonly α = 0.05) "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.jmp.com/en/statistics-knowledge-portal/inferential-statistics/hypothesis-testing","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"jmp"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Critical value"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Boundary of the \"critical region\" where you reject H₀"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Decision"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Either \"reject H₀\" or \"fail to reject H₀\" (never \"accept H₀\")/09:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Hypothesis_Testing/9.01:"},{"type":"text","text":"Introduction_to_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hypothesis testing validates claims and decisions in ML:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ML Application"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"How hypothesis testing applies"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Model Comparison"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Test if Model A is significantly better than Model B"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Feature Selection"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Test if a feature has statistically significant effect on outcome"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"A/B Testing"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Compare two versions of a model/system in production"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Quality Assurance"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Verify if model performance meets requirements"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Safety Validation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Test if generative AI outputs are safe/appropriate"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Real example"},{"type":"text","text":": When comparing GPT-4 to GPT-3.5, you use hypothesis testing to determine if the observed accuracy difference (e.g., 85% vs. 82%) is statistically significant or just random noise."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When a hypothesis test happens"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: Formulate hypotheses\n  H₀: No effect (e.g., \"no difference between models\")\n  H₁: Effect exists (e.g., \"Model A is better\") [web:242]\n\nStep 2: Choose significance level (α)\n  Common values: α = 0.05 (5%), α = 0.01 (1%)\n  Determines how much evidence you need [web:241][web:242]\n\nStep 3: Collect sample data\n  Run experiment or gather data from population [web:239][web:242]\n\nStep 4: Calculate test statistic\n  Compute statistic from data (t, z, χ², F) [web:239][web:242]\n\nStep 5: Find p-value\n  P(observing this data | H₀ is true) [web:242][web:245]\n\nStep 6: Make decision\n  If p < α: Reject H₀ (statistically significant)\n  If p ≥ α: Fail to reject H₀ (not significant) [web:241][web:242]\n\nStep 7: Interpret results\n  Draw conclusions about population [web:242]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common hypothesis tests"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"z-test"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Population variance known OR large sample (n ≥ 30)./12:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"},{"type":"text","text":"Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test statistic"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"z = (sample_mean - population_mean) / (σ / √n)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where σ = population standard deviation, n = sample size./12:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"},{"type":"text","text":"Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Distribution"},{"type":"text","text":": Standard Normal (Z Normal(0, 1))"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": Testing if average height differs from 170cm (σ known = 10cm)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"t-test"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Population variance unknown AND small sample (n < 30)./12:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"},{"type":"text","text":"Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test statistic"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"t = (sample_mean - population_mean) / (s / √n)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where s = sample standard deviation./12:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"},{"type":"text","text":"Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Distribution"},{"type":"text","text":": Student's t-distribution with df = n - 1 degrees of freedom"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Types of t-tests"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"One-sample t-test"},{"type":"text","text":": Compare sample mean to known value\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Two-sample t-test"},{"type":"text","text":": Compare two independent groups (most common in ML)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Paired t-test"},{"type":"text","text":": Compare same group before/after treatment"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": Comparing Model A vs. Model B accuracy with 20 test samples each./12:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"},{"type":"text","text":"Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chi-square (χ²) test"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Testing if observed frequencies match expected frequencies (categorical data)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test statistic"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"χ² = Σ (observed - expected)² / expected"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Distribution"},{"type":"text","text":": Chi-square distribution with df = categories - 1"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": Testing if a classification model's predictions match expected distribution"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"F-test"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use"},{"type":"text","text":": Comparing variance of two populations"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test statistic"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"F = variance₁ / variance₂"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Distribution"},{"type":"text","text":": F-distribution with df₁, df₂"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": Testing if two models have equal variance in predictions"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Python implementation"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two-sample t-test (comparing two models):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np\nfrom scipy import stats\n\n# Model accuracies from 100 test samples each\nmodel_A = np.random.normal(loc=0.85, scale=0.05, size=100)\nmodel_B = np.random.normal(loc=0.82, scale=0.05, size=100)\n\n# Perform two-sample t-test\nt_stat, p_value = stats.ttest_ind(model_A, model_B)\n\nprint(f\"t-statistic: {t_stat:.3f}\")\nprint(f\"p-value: {p_value:.3f}\")\n\n# Decision\nalpha = 0.05\nif p_value < alpha:\n    print(\"Reject H₀: Model A is significantly better than Model B\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Fail to reject H₀: No significant difference\")"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"One-sample t-test (testing if mean ≠ 0.80):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np\nfrom scipy import stats\n\n# Model accuracies\naccuracies = np.array([0.85, 0.87, 0.83, 0.86, 0.88])\n\n# Test if mean accuracy > 0.80\nt_stat, p_value = stats.ttest_1samp(accuracies, popmean=0.80)\n\n# For one-tailed test (mean > 0.80), divide p-value by 2\np_one_tailed = p_value / 2\n\nprint(f\"t-statistic: {t_stat:.3f}\")\nprint(f\"p-value (one-tailed): {p_one_tailed:.3f}\")"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Z-test (large sample, known variance):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np\nfrom scipy import stats\n\n# Sample data\nsample_mean = 0.85\npopulation_mean = 0.80\nsigma = 0.05  # Known population std\nn = 100  # Large sample\n\n# Calculate z-statistic\nz_stat = (sample_mean - population_mean) / (sigma / np.sqrt(n))\n\n# p-value (two-tailed)\np_value = 2 * (1 - stats.norm.cdf(abs(z_stat)))\n\nprint(f\"z-statistic: {z_stat:.3f}\")\nprint(f\"p-value: {p_value:.3f}\")"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Interpreting results"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"p-value interpretation:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"p-value = probability that observed effect occurred by chance if no true effect exists\n\nConventionally:\n  p < 0.05: statistically significant (reject H₀)\n  p < 0.01: highly significant\n  p ≥ 0.05: not significant (fail to reject H₀) [web:208][web:242]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Decision rule:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"If p < α: Reject H₀ → Evidence supports H₁\nIf p ≥ α: Fail to reject H₀ → Insufficient evidence for H₁\n\nNote: \"Fail to reject\" ≠ \"accept H₀\"; we just don't have enough evidence [web:238][web:241]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confidence interval connection:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"A 95% confidence interval includes the null hypothesis value if p ≥ 0.05\nA 95% confidence interval excludes the null hypothesis value if p < 0.05 [web:202][web:206]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CI provides more information about "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"precision"},{"type":"text","text":" than p-value alone."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common mistakes — Pitfalls to avoid"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistake"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Correction"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Accepting H₀\""}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Say \"fail to reject H₀\" instead; we never prove H₀ true/09:"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"Hypothesis_Testing/9.01:"},{"type":"text","text":"Introduction_to_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Confusing p-value with effect size"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Small p-value ≠ large effect; check effect size separately"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Using wrong α level"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Choose α based on context (0.05 common, but 0.01 for medical safety) "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.jmp.com/en/statistics-knowledge-portal/inferential-statistics/hypothesis-testing","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"jmp"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ignoring sample size"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Small samples → harder to detect real effects; large samples → can detect trivial effects"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Multiple testing problem"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Testing many hypotheses increases false positives; use corrections (Bonferroni)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hypothesis testing = statistical decision"},{"type":"text","text":": Reject H₀ or fail to reject H₀ based on evidence "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.jmp.com/en/statistics-knowledge-portal/inferential-statistics/hypothesis-testing","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"jmp"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bol